ve at least 3 encs, 3 wizzies, then all the rest of the assorted mages, druids, clerics tossing out their nukes as well.  Druids love the opportunity =P<br><br>Bring a rogue for the trap at the palace ent btw.<br><br>Important thing is to move quickly quickly quickly.  Obviously you're going to have a large amount of people if you're attempting the royals so I would make a shout letting your raid know about the incoming AE pull.  When you do it, just like you do an AE Fear raid (or I do anyway), have all the encs and AE casters stand to the front so the rest don't get in the way.  Bring the biggest pull you possibly can so you can clear a large amount.  Once all the mobs are there and the nuke has been called have the melee crowd around and pick targets w/ the MA and help clear them out.  Then while your AE casters med, pull normally and have the rest of the raid distpatch until you can have your AE groups ready again.<br><br>Good luck!!<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.home.net/erichuinker/insanity.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukrela.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krela</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/21/02 6:07:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.unresolved.org/images/everquest/lightn1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for advice for Chardok Royals AoE Style</span><hr size=1> We did AE Royals this past sunday. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magusamicitia.co.uk/screens/royals.html">check out the screenshots</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br>I got the killshots on all 3 royals and got a nice lil insignia protector as a reward :)<br><br>AE Royals is the only way to go IMO, just remember that when you are left with 2-3 straglers after the AE you _MUST_ snare them otherwise you get another train to deal with when you're oom :)<br><br>It's not so bad though... <br><br>1) ae library, <br>2) pull herb room to library ae them, <br>3) get levitate/DMF<br>4) move into herby<br>5) pull king, ae/tank king + adds<br>6) move into king room (stand in kings pit otherwise you risk getting gfluxed back up into herby and pulling a rather nasty &amp; large unexpected train).<br>7) Prep up for queen, kill any repops in king room/corridor.<br>8) Move into queen room hallway, put casters just inside the door with LoS to queen, get enchanters to target a guard each<br>9) Melee bum rush the queen, nuke at 80% - enchanters mez guards.<br>10) Kill guards<br>11) This is where the real fun starts, you now have an hour maybe 1:30 to pull nice trains and have some AE fun.<br>12) Keep king timed, pull king room repops just before king pops and AE them<br>13) Pull king solo + kill<br>14) 5 mins before next queen pop go to step 8.<br><br>This is relatively low stress, fun and easy. We got 3 kings 2 queens and 2 princes on sunday - and strange as it sounds queen room is by far the safest place to be down there.<br><br>That is AE royals :)<br> <p><center><img src="http://homepage.ntlworld.com/redcelt/magus/sig_persephonne_60.jpg" border='0'><br><font size='1'>Do not meddle in the affairs of Wizards, for they are subtle and quick to anger...<br><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4244'>Persephonne</a> - Sorcerer | <a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4260'>Krela